article.headline: South Florida takes down South Carolina State 96-52

images.caption: South Carolina State Bulldogs vs. South Florida Bulls: Full Highlights

article.linkText: South Florida takes down South Carolina State 96-52
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- — Chris Youngblood's 19 points helped South Florida defeat South Carolina State 96-52 on Thursday night. Youngblood shot 6 for 9 (2 for 3 from 3-point range) and 5 of 6 from the free throw line for the Bulls (1-0). Selton Miguel scored 18 points, shooting 7 for 11, including 4 for 6 from beyond the arc. Sam Hines Jr. went 5 of 6 from the field to finish with 12 points. Mitchel Taylor led the way for the Bulldogs (1-1) with 11 points and three steals. Caleb McCarty added eight points and two steals for South Carolina State. NEXT UP Up next for South Florida is a matchup Wednesday with Central Michigan at home. South Carolina State hosts North Florida on Monday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
